bug.short_desc: Embed canvas makes all other controls invisible on ios7

long_desc.thetext:
You need ipad with ios7. - Open safari and open page http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/widgetbrowser/ - Choose tab Embed
You will see that only canvas and few labels are visible. Bug can be reproduced only on ios7.
If you remove tag canvas with remote debugging help, everything returns to normal.
This does not affect an emulated IOS 7 device using the simulator. Seems to pop up on real hardware, only.
I can reproduce it on simulator with google maps in my app. See my last screenshot.
Thanks for the report. We will check that...
Just updated to iOS 7.0.3 - Unfortunately still reproducible for me :(

Workaround: Change z-index of some containers up from canvas and make it "z-index:-10" For example: on page http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/widgetbrowser/ you need to change only one Scroll container. But in my own project I've changed 2 containers. So, you need to experiment a little.
Don't know why it helps.

Yes, I found a IOS 7 rendering laziness related blog post some days ago:
http://onderhond.com/features/css-bugs
Had no time to experiment with it yet, but I think Apple should fix it. Question is when - and if.

Just tried it and it seems not straight forward to find *which* containers to adjust the z-index. While things changed a little after adding it to the canvas containing element itself, it didn't fix everything. There were still some navigation elements invisible. I needed to step up further in the widget hierachy until it fully worked.
*** Bug 7813 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

We can workaround that issue by adding a "-webkit-backface-visibility: hidden" to the root of the application. Added that for the inline and application root which should fix all desktop like apps.
